  <steps>
    <step>Read SpaarkeAuthProvider.ts lines 44-83 carefully — note the MSAL Configuration object. Document INV-1, INV-2, INV-3 as inline preserved-by-lift comments in the new code.</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/src/strategies/AuthStrategy.ts: interface AuthStrategy { name: string; acquire(): Promise&lt;TokenResult&gt;; clearCache(): void; }. Define TokenResult { accessToken: string; expiresOn: number; tenantId?: string; }.</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/src/strategies/BrowserMsalStrategy.ts as a stub that implements AuthStrategy. Constructor takes IAuthConfig. Lift the MSAL Configuration object from SpaarkeAuthProvider lines 44-83 verbatim (cacheLocation: 'localStorage', storeAuthStateInCookie: true, authority from resolveDefaultAuthority). Wire to existing MsalSilentStrategy + MsalPopupStrategy internally for now (full refactor in 011).</step>
    <step>Refactor SpaarkeAuthProvider.ts: keep constructor + 6-strategy orchestration but make it strategy-agnostic — accept an AuthStrategy implementation via constructor. Remove the old constructor lines that build msalConfig directly (now done in BrowserMsalStrategy).</step>
    <step>Delete src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/src/strategies/BridgeStrategy.ts, src/strategies/XrmStrategy.ts, src/tokenBridge.ts.</step>
    <step>Update src/types.ts: remove window.__SPAARKE_BFF_TOKEN__ global declaration. Add AccessToken branded type stub (for use in 013).</step>
    <step>Update src/index.ts: remove tokenBridge exports (publishToken, readBridgeToken, clearBridgeToken). Add AuthStrategy export.</step>
    <step>Update initAuth.ts: instantiate BrowserMsalStrategy by default; SpaarkeAuthProvider receives it.</step>
    <step>Run tsc --noEmit to verify clean compile. Run existing tests to verify no behavior regression (existing CacheStrategy + SessionStorageStrategy unit tests should still pass).</step>
  </steps>
